description.narrative: Despite COVID19-related delays, progress was made on integrated early childhood education and expansion of Social Emotional Learning training for pre-school teachers. Support for the Southeast Asia Primary Learning Metrics (SEA-PLM) continued with preparations for the main survey report. Covid-19 response became a top priority under this output, with significant resources mobilsed to procure basic hygiene supplies for schools and for creating inclusive distance learning programmes. Progress was observed in new distance teaching and learning approaches and teaching at pre-primary, primary and secondary levels, as well as inclusion of learning for children with disabilities and children from ethnic minority communities. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:21/08/2020
